**Class Definition and Overview**  
We will construct a C++ class named `UndergraduateStudentProfile` that encapsulates the essential attributes and behaviors of a university undergraduate student. The class will contain the following private member variables:  
- `std::string fullName` – to store the student's complete legal name  
- `std::string studentID` – a unique identifier code for each student  
- `double gpa` – the cumulative academic metric known as the grade point average  

The class will also include public accessor and mutator methods for each of these attributes, ensuring encapsulation and data integrity.

*highlighted section*  
**Implementation of the Class**  
Here is the complete implementation of the `UndergraduateStudentProfile` class in C++:

```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <string>

class UndergraduateStudentProfile {
private:
    std::string fullName;
    std::string studentID;
    double gpa;

public:
    // Constructor
    UndergraduateStudentProfile(const std::string& name, const std::string& id, double gpa)
        : fullName(name), studentID(id), gpa(gpa) {}

    // Accessor methods
    std::string getName() const { return fullName; }
    std::string getID() const { return studentID; }
    double getGPA() const { return gpa; }

    // Mutator methods
    void setName(const std::string& name) { fullName = name; }
    void setID(const std::string& id) { studentID = id; }
    void setGPA(double gpa) { this->gpa = gpa; }

    // Display method
    void displayProfile() const {
        std::cout << "Student Name: " << fullName << std::endl;
        std::cout << "Student ID: " << studentID << std::endl;
        std::cout << "GPA: " << gpa << std::endl;
    }
};
```

